snippet: With his legal status resolved and final ballots due Monday, many involved in the voting process say Jameis Winston is likely to become the second freshman to win the Heisman Trophy.
abstract: State Attorney's office for Florida's Second Judicial Circuit announces that Florida State quarterback Jameis Winston will not be charged with sexual assault, based on lack of evidence; with his legal status resolved, many of the 928 voters responsible for handing out the coveted Heisman Trophy say path for Winston to become second freshman in history to win trophy has now been cleared.

byline.original: By JOE DRAPE and BILL PENNINGTON

lead_paragraph: With his legal status resolved and final ballots due Monday, many involved in the voting process say Jameis Winston is likely to become the second freshman to win the Heisman Trophy.

headline.main: After Decision on Winston, Voters Must Make a Call
headline.print_headline: After Decision on Winston, Voters Must Make a Call
